{"type": "article", "id": 5076, "title": "插画师如何回应「《查理周刊》事件」", "description": "Best On The Web 是一个推荐性栏目，每个工作日我们会从互联网世界中找出最好看的内容，希望这个栏目让我们始终与阅读、知识和美好在一起。", "date": "2015-01-09T08:33:26Z", "super_tag": null, "tags": [{"id": 5943, "name": "Charlie Hebdo"}, {"id": 1124, "name": "巴黎"}, {"id": 999, "name": "讽刺"}, {"id": 2059, "name": "插画"}, {"id": 2485, "name": "illustration"}], "category": 12, "author": 13, "comment_count": 2, "praise_count": 9, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160604222345mrP7fJjTbZVKUxsA.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong>It's Nice That</strong>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong><a href=\"http://www.itsnicethat.com/articles/je-suis-charlie-responses\" target=\"_blank\">How illustrators responded to the Charlie Hebdo attack in Paris</a></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t插画师很少占据中心话题，这一次关于法国讽刺刊物 Charlie Hebdo 的不幸除外。因为长期对伊斯兰群体的讽刺性展示，这个杂志社包括 Cabu、Wolinski、Tignous 三名插画师在内的 12 人遇难。一些插画师在社交网络上发表了如下一些作品，来表达自己的情绪和态度。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222339Xb1qepNVchkuySPZ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.68125\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><strong><a href=\"http://www.belltoons.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\">Steven Bell</a></strong>, 《卫报》</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222340Rd9cLZaeYEQhI3v6.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.6375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><br>\r\n</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><a href=\"http://i100.independent.co.uk/article/the-moving-tributes-to-the-victims-of-the-charlie-hebdo-shooting--lJVs7t8dcx\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Dave Brown, 《独立报》</strong></a></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222340aCP9WFp6IG1quoHs.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.9984375\" data-format=\"png\"><br>\r\n</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<i><strong><a href=\"http://www.jeanjullien.com/\" target=\"_blank\">法国插画师 Jean Jullien</a></strong></i> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<i><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222341TMzK9I7EkRJXWqFr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.834375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><br>\r\n</i> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><strong>智利插画师 <a href=\"http://instagram.com/malaimagen\" target=\"_blank\">Mala Imagen</a></strong></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222341T5ksuBCE6LzvjOl1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.3984375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><br>\r\n</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><strong><a href=\"http://www.rubenoppenheimer.com/\" target=\"_blank\">荷兰政治漫画家 Ruben. L. Oppenheimer </a></strong></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222342hLKisHZaEQu1SN3y.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.9171875\" data-format=\"jpeg\"><br>\r\n</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><strong><a href=\"http://www.yoopdeloop.com/\" target=\"_blank\">荷兰插画师 Joep Bertrams </a></strong></em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<em><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222343e5BjHzDyiKWVgovX.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.0\" data-format=\"png\"><br>\r\n</em> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t年轻的插画师<a href=\"http://hattiestewart.com/\" target=\"_blank\"> <strong>Hattie Stewart </strong></a><strong> </strong>现居住在伦敦，画风浓烈活泼，多与时尚品牌合作。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222343trCFpAoN5WkIYBu1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.4828125\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong><a href=\"http://oleismos.blogspot.com/\" target=\"_blank\">智利插画师 Francisco J. Olea </a></strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222343GlRkKnydpZDof8b3.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.6515625\" data-format=\"png\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong><a href=\"http://tango2010weibo.tumblr.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Tango</a> </strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t<strong><img src=\"img/uploads/20160604222344T9mqPcZxHO4Bb8V3.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.8265625\" data-format=\"png\"><br>\r\n</strong> \r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t这幅由 Robert Mankoff 创作的插画来自于 2012 年 9 月的《纽约客》，同时成为了这一次《纽约客》对此事件的回应。\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"white-space:normal;margin-bottom:16px !important;\">\r\n\t而一些媒体，<strong><a href=\"http://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/style/news-organizations-wrestle-with-whether-to-publish-charlie-hebdo-cartoons-after-attack/2015/01/07/841e9c8c-96bc-11e4-8005-1924ede3e54a_story.html?utm_source=nextdraft&amp;utm_medium=email\" target=\"_blank\">徘徊于是否要在这次灾难事件之后，继续发表来自 Charlie Hebdo 的漫画</a></strong>。\r\n</p>\n\n\n"}